    "description": {
      "value": "<div>\n<div class=\"rd__b  rd__b--3\">\n<p>When you hit a creature with a weapon attack, you can expend one superiority die to attempt to frighten the target. You add the superiority die to the attack's damage roll, and the target must make a Wisdom saving throw. On a failed save, it is @condition[frightened] of you until the end of your next turn.</p>\n<div class=\"rd__spc-inline-post\">Â </div>\n<div class=\"rd__spc-inline-post\"><strong>Use your superiority die during the attack, then use this special action afterwards.</strong></div>\n</div>\n</div>",
